definitions.definition: The surgical excision of the foreskin and usually all or most of the penile frenulum .

subdefinitions.definition: Other surgeries involving the incision or partial excision of the foreskin or penile frenulum without total posthetomy .
examples: The ancient Egyptians practiced circumcision by creating a dorsal incision in the foreskin.

definitions.definition: The surgical excision of the clitoral hood of the clitoris ; female circumcision .
The surgical excision of the clitoris; clitoridectomy .
